(9, 'General Solid Unit', NULL, 'general-solid-unit', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=U_cnIDlN0Wc', 'Healthcare Pharmaceuticals Limited (HPL), located in Rajendrapur, Gazipur, Bangladesh, operates a world-class General Solid Production facility, spanning 6,955 sq.m. The site is GMP-compliant and certified by regulatory bodies including TGA (Australia) and NPRA (Malaysia). A new Mega Site, launched in 2024, adds 7,400 sq.m. of production space, with further expansion planned. HPL manufactures tablets, capsules, powders, and effervescent tablets using advanced machinery. With a strong focus on quality management, research & development, and global compliance, HPL continues to expand its footprint, providing high-quality pharmaceutical products worldwide.', '<p>Healthcare Pharmaceuticals Limited (HPL) is a prominent player in Bangladesh&#39;s pharmaceutical industry, with a world-class manufacturing facility located in Rajendrapur, Gazipur, approximately 50 kilometers north of Dhaka. The total premises cover an expansive 31,200 square meters, with a covered area of 6,955 square meters, surrounded by a green environment of natural forests and fields. This location provides an ideal, pollution-free environment, with no sources of dust or smoke nearby, ensuring optimal production conditions. The internal infrastructure is well-designed, featuring cement roads for internal transportation and landscaped unused land, all secured by a high brick wall with metal grills.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>HPL&rsquo;s General Solid Production unit is spread across two multi-story buildings. The facility is equipped with state-of-the-art manufacturing and packaging machinery, designed in compliance with international Good Manufacturing Practices (GMP) guidelines. The unit is supported by cutting-edge HVAC and Water Systems, as well as stringent health and safety standards to ensure the highest levels of product quality and worker safety. The production unit manufactures a diverse range of products, including tablets, capsules, powders for suspension, sachets, and effervescent tablets, meeting both local and international demand.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In terms of global regulatory compliance, the existing facility is certified by several leading international regulatory bodies, such as TGA (Australia), NPRA (Malaysia), MCAZ (Zimbabwe), PPB (Kenya), TFDA (Tanzania), and SBDMA (Yemen). These certifications demonstrate HPL&rsquo;s commitment to maintaining the highest standards of quality and safety in pharmaceutical production. In 2024, HPL inaugurated a new production facility, the Mega Site, which is already operational and undergoing local regulatory audits. The company has ambitious plans to expand the new Mega Site&rsquo;s GMP certifications to include approvals from international regulatory bodies, further enhancing its global reach.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The total production space in the first building is 5,000 square meters, while the new Mega Site adds an additional 7,400 square meters. The Mega Site also includes an additional 7,400 square meters reserved for future expansion, reflecting HPL&rsquo;s forward-thinking approach and readiness to scale its operations to meet increasing global demand.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>HPL&rsquo;s production capabilities are supported by advanced machinery sourced from world-renowned manufacturers. The facility is equipped with high-speed, high-capacity machinery for various processes, such as dispensing, granulation, blending, tablet compression, capsule filling, and packaging. This includes equipment like Fabtech &amp; Klenzaid Dispensing Booths, GEA Integrated Granulation Lines, Fette Tablet Compression Machines, and Syntegon Capsule Filling Machines. The company&#39;s packaging capabilities are also robust, featuring blister machines from leading brands like Uhlmann and Noack, as well as cartoning and foil printing machines, ensuring efficient, high-quality packaging for its products.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Additionally, HPL places great emphasis on its Quality Management System (QMS) and Research &amp; Development (R&amp;D), continuously updating these systems to ensure compliance with evolving regulatory standards and to foster innovation in pharmaceutical formulations and processes. The company&rsquo;s commitment to quality is further reflected in its investment in modern HVAC systems, ensuring that environmental conditions in the production area are tightly controlled to prevent contamination and maintain product integrity.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>HPL&rsquo;s journey began in 2000 as a licensee of F. Hoffmann-La Roche, Switzerland, and has since grown into an independent, internationally recognized pharmaceutical company by 2006. The company&rsquo;s growth trajectory and ongoing investments in modern facilities and technology are testaments to its dedication to providing high-quality pharmaceutical products both locally and internationally. With over 705 non-management employees and 53 management staff, HPL is well-positioned to continue its expansion and uphold its reputation as a leader in Bangladesh&rsquo;s pharmaceutical sector.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As the company looks to the future, the planned expansion of its Mega Site and the continuous upgrading of its facilities ensure that HPL remains at the forefront of the pharmaceutical industry in Bangladesh and beyond. The company&#39;s vision is to expand its global footprint by continually enhancing its manufacturing capabilities, complying with the highest international standards, and providing high-quality, affordable medicines to markets worldwide.</p>', 'dafault.png', '2024-10-06 09:10:19', '2024-10-15 13:26:22'),
(10, 'Oncology Unit', NULL, 'oncology-unit', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=aWuVpb4Xw3o', 'Healthcare Pharmaceuticals Limited (HPL) has developed a state-of-the-art Oncology Manufacturing Unit, designed in collaboration with Australian consultancy APC. The facility specializes in high-containment production of anti-cancer products, including Oral Solid Dosage (OSD) and injectables, for both local and international markets. Spanning four levels and 18,648 square feet, the unit houses advanced R&D and Quality Control laboratories, as well as high-tech equipment for precise production. Certified by GMP in Bangladesh, Nepal, and Yemen, HPL is also working towards EU, US, and ANVISA certifications. The unit maintains stringent quality standards and is expanding its global market presence.', '<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Healthcare Pharmaceuticals Limited (HPL) has established a cutting-edge, state-of-the-art Oncology Manufacturing Unit designed to meet both local and international demand for high-quality oncology products. This specialized unit was developed in collaboration with Australian consultancy APC and features a high-containment processing and testing facility with 100% isolators to ensure safe production of sensitive anti-cancer drugs. The facility is strategically designed to manufacture and supply Oral Solid Dosage (OSD) forms, including tablets and capsules, as well as injectable products such as liquid and lyophilized injections. HPL&rsquo;s Oncology Manufacturing Unit is not only a testament to the company&#39;s commitment to innovation and advanced technology, but also to its goal of expanding its presence in the global pharmaceutical industry by maintaining rigorous safety and quality standards.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>The facility itself is housed in a four-level building, each floor dedicated to specific production and research functions. Level-1, the Ground Floor, is the manufacturing hub, where all anti-cancer products, including tablets, capsules, and injectables, are produced within a secure containment system. This floor also serves as a warehouse, ensuring efficient storage and distribution of finished products. Level-2, or the 1st Floor, is exclusively dedicated to the HVAC system, which maintains a controlled and sterile environment, critical for the safe production of oncology products. Level-3, the 2nd Floor, is home to the Oncology Research &amp; Development (R&amp;D) Laboratory, Oncology Quality Control (QC) Laboratory, as well as the Water Plant, Building Management System (BMS), and other essential departments, including the Stability Chamber, Filter Cleaning Room, and offices for Quality Assurance (QA) and engineering teams. Finally, Level-4, the 3rd Floor, houses the Oncology Microbiology Laboratory and a General R&amp;D Laboratory (Center of Excellence), equipped with its own dedicated HVAC system. Together, these facilities span a total of 18,648 square feet, offering ample space for production, quality control, research, and administrative functions.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>The Oncology Unit is not only state-of-the-art in design but also GMP-certified (Good Manufacturing Practices) by the Directorate General of Drug Administration (DGDA) under the Ministry of Health &amp; Family Welfare of Bangladesh, as well as the Department of Drug Administration in Nepal, and the Ministry of Public Health and Population Supreme Board of Drugs &amp; Medical Appliances in Yemen. These certifications are a testament to the high-quality standards maintained by the facility. Moreover, HPL is actively working towards obtaining additional GMP certifications from EU GMP, ANVISA, and the US FDA, aiming to expand its market reach and enhance its competitiveness on the global stage.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>The Oncology Manufacturing Unit is equipped with advanced machinery sourced from world-leading manufacturers to ensure efficient, high-precision production. Key machinery includes a Granulation Line from GEA with capacities ranging from 60L to 300L, a Capsule Filling Machine from Karnavati Engineering with a production rate of 3,000 pieces per hour, and a Labcoat IIX Coating Machine from Ohara, Canada, which features multiple pan sizes to accommodate different production scales. Additional equipment, such as the FAMAR TF120 Blister Machine from Italy and the Lyophilizer from Telstar, Spain, underscores the facility&rsquo;s ability to produce and package high-quality, stable oncology products at scale. The Autoclave Machine from Zirbus, Germany, with its 318-liter capacity, ensures proper sterilization of equipment and products, while the Sterile Filtration Isolator from Fabtech, India, maintains a contaminant-free environment during production.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>To ensure product quality and compliance with international standards, HPL follows a stringent Quality Management System (QMS) based on industry-leading guidelines such as EudraLex Volume 4, 21 CFR 210 &amp; 211, PIC/S, ANVISA, WHO, ICH, and ISO standards. Various QMS tools are in place, including systems for handling deviations, change control, quality risk management, product complaints, out-of-specification (OOS) and out-of-trend (OOT) results, self-inspections, product recalls, and corrective action and preventive action (CAPA) management. The company is also transitioning towards a paperless QMS, utilizing electronic Quality Management Systems (eQMS), Document Management Systems (DMS), and Learning Management Systems (LMS). Finished products are released through SAP, ensuring seamless integration with the company&rsquo;s enterprise resource planning (ERP) system.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>In addition to its state-of-the-art manufacturing capabilities, HPL&rsquo;s Research &amp; Development (R&amp;D) team is continuously working to develop new oncology products for both local and international markets. The R&amp;D department follows current guidelines to ensure the development of high-quality products that meet the stringent requirements of regulated markets. The facility also employs advanced containment systems to handle high-potency products while maintaining Occupational Exposure Band (OEB) levels 4 and 5 at various production stages, ensuring the safety of both workers and products.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Since its establishment in 2015, HPL&rsquo;s Oncology Manufacturing Unit has become a key player in the pharmaceutical industry, producing innovative anti-cancer drugs that meet global standards. With further GMP certifications on the horizon, a strong focus on quality management, and a commitment to ongoing R&amp;D, the Oncology Unit is poised to play a pivotal role in the future growth of HPL and its ability to provide life-saving treatments to patients worldwide.</strong></p>', 'dafault.png', '2024-10-06 09:17:46', '2024-10-06 15:03:55'),
(11, 'Hormone Unit', NULL, 'hormone-unit', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5NSxhRWpbFk', 'Healthcare Pharmaceuticals Limited (HPL) has established a state-of-the-art Hormone Unit dedicated to the safe and efficient production of hormone products. The facility consists of three levels, including production areas for non-contraceptive and contraceptive oral solid products, along with a sterile manufacturing space. HPL holds GMP approvals from the DGDA and aims to achieve EU, FDA, and ANVISA certifications. Equipped with advanced machinery and a comprehensive quality management system, HPL adheres to strict safety standards, maintaining OEB levels 4 and 5. The Hormone Unit exemplifies HPL\'s commitment to delivering high-quality pharmaceutical products for local and international markets.', '<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Healthcare Pharmaceuticals Limited (HPL) is committed to establishing a cutting-edge Hormone Unit that integrates advanced building structures, utilities, and equipment to ensure the safe, efficient, and reliable handling of its products. The facility features a containment system designed to achieve an Operator Exposure Limit (OEL) classified as OEB-5, utilizing isolation technology to maintain stringent safety standards.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>The Hormone Unit comprises three levels, with each floor dedicated to specific manufacturing processes. Level 1 focuses on the production of non-contraceptive oral solid hormone products, equipped with independent loading and unloading systems, an HVAC system, and a comprehensive water distribution system. To ensure safety, firefighting equipment is strategically installed throughout the facility. Level 2 is currently under design and will be dedicated to the manufacture of non-contraceptive sterile hormone products. Level 3 is designated for the production of contraceptive oral solid hormone products and also features containment systems, independent loading/unloading facilities, HVAC, and water distribution systems.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>HPL&rsquo;s Hormone Unit has received GMP approval from the DGDA under the Ministry of Health &amp; Family Welfare, Government of the People&#39;s Republic of Bangladesh. The facility aims to achieve upcoming GMP certifications from EU, FDA, and ANVISA to ensure compliance with international standards. The types of products manufactured include tablets and injections, with a total production area of 26,000 square meters per floor.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Since its establishment in November 2018, HPL has developed this dedicated facility for hormone products, ensuring complete separation for storage, production, packaging, and laboratory operations. This strategic design mitigates any risks associated with cross-contamination. The facility employs a specialized workforce, consisting of 2 management and 13 non-management personnel for hormone contraceptive production, and 2 management and 17 non-management personnel for non-contraceptive production.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>The Hormone Unit is equipped with state-of-the-art machinery sourced from reputable manufacturers worldwide. The dispensing isolators, granulation lines, and compression machines are designed to ensure optimal production efficiency. The quality management system (QMS) at HPL adheres to multiple regulatory guidelines, including EudraLex Volume 4 Good Manufacturing Practices, 21 CFR 210 &amp; 211, PIC/S, ANVISA, WHO, ICH, and ISO. Various QMS tools are implemented to maintain product quality, and HPL is transitioning to a paperless quality management system, utilizing eQMS, DMS, and LMS for streamlined operations.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Research and development activities are ongoing, focusing on hormone replacement therapy and local product development, all in line with current guidelines. The facility&rsquo;s commitment to safety and quality ensures that all products are manufactured under stringent conditions, maintaining OEB levels 4 and 5 at different stages of production. This robust infrastructure positions HPL as a leader in the pharmaceutical industry, dedicated to delivering high-quality hormone products to meet the needs of both local and international markets.</strong></p>', 'dafault.png', '2024-10-06 09:28:47', '2024-10-06 09:28:47'),
(12, 'General Sterile + Ophthalmic Unit', NULL, 'general-sterile-ophthalmic-unit', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dD6a6-l9mTE', 'Since inception HPL has been manufacturing generic products in different therapeutic classes. Our current manufacturing facilities cover Oral solids and semisolid dosage forms meeting international GMP compliances. Last year HPL has established world class and state of the art sterile facility for generic formulation in the same premises. Major product categories belong to small volume parenterals, lyophilized powder in glass vials, sterile ophthalmic solution, pre-filled syringes for recombinant products & Metered Dose Inhaler (MDI). HPL is humbly thankful to all concerned and all experts from home and abroad for their contribution to establishing such world class facility in the country. With the active support and cooperation this facility will make sure to provide with high quality and affordable medicines to all people around the globe.', '<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Since inception HPL has been manufacturing generic products in different therapeutic classes. Our current manufacturing facilities cover Oral solids and semisolid dosage forms meeting international GMP compliances.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Last year HPL has established world class and state of the art sterile facility for generic formulation in the same premises. Major product categories belong to small volume parenterals, lyophilized powder in glass vials, sterile ophthalmic solution, pre-filled syringes for recombinant products &amp; Metered Dose Inhaler (MDI).</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>HPL is humbly thankful to all concerned and all experts from home and abroad for their contribution to establishing such world class facility in the country. With the active support and cooperation this facility will make sure to provide with high quality and affordable medicines to all people around the globe.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Since its inception, Healthcare Pharmaceuticals Limited (HPL) has been dedicated to manufacturing high-quality generic products across various therapeutic classes. Currently, HPL&#39;s manufacturing facilities specialize in oral solids and semi-solid dosage forms that adhere to international Good Manufacturing Practices (GMP). In recent developments, HPL has established a state-of-the-art sterile facility for generic formulations within the same premises, significantly enhancing its production capabilities. This new facility focuses on key product categories, including small volume parenterals, lyophilized powders in glass vials, sterile ophthalmic solutions, pre-filled syringes for recombinant products, and Metered Dose Inhalers (MDIs).</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>The General Sterile + Ophthalmic Unit consists of three levels designed to optimize manufacturing efficiency. The first floor is specifically utilized for the production of various sterile products, featuring a dedicated material loading and unloading system, an advanced HVAC system, and a robust water distribution system. Firefighting equipment has been strategically installed to address any potential hazards, ensuring a safe working environment.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>HPL has received GMP approval from the Directorate General of Drug Administration (DGDA) in Bangladesh, underscoring its commitment to maintaining high-quality standards. Although there are currently no upcoming GMP plans, HPL remains focused on expanding its product range, which includes liquid injections, lyophilized injections, prefilled syringes, and ophthalmic products.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Operationally, the facility boasts a substantial floor area of 1,310 square meters, which accommodates a variety of advanced machinery. Notable equipment includes the Adam Manufacturing Vessel for liquid formulations, a Rota washing and depyrogenation machine, and cutting-edge filling machines sourced from leading manufacturers in Germany and South Korea. This equipment enables HPL to achieve high production capacities, ensuring efficiency and quality in every product batch.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Established in December 2012, the facility began operations in early 2013, with liquid injection and ophthalmic product manufacturing commencing in January, followed by lyophilized injections and prefilled syringes in March. HPL&#39;s workforce for the General Sterile + Ophthalmic Unit comprises a management team of nine professionals and a dedicated non-management staff of 100 individuals, all working together to uphold HPL&#39;s high standards.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>To guarantee the highest quality products, HPL adheres to rigorous Quality Management System (QMS) guidelines, including EudraLex Volume 4, 21 CFR 210 &amp; 211, and other international standards. Various QMS tools are utilized to monitor deviations, change controls, quality risks, and product complaints, reinforcing HPL&#39;s dedication to quality assurance. The company is currently implementing a paperless QMS, utilizing electronic quality management systems (eQMS), document management systems (DMS), and laboratory management systems (LMS) for improved efficiency.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>In conclusion, HPL expresses sincere gratitude to all contributors, both local and international, for their efforts in establishing this world-class facility. With continued support and collaboration, HPL aims to provide high-quality, affordable medicines to people around the globe, ensuring that healthcare needs are met effectively and efficiently.</strong></p>', 'dafault.png', '2024-10-06 09:32:23', '2024-10-06 09:32:23'),
(14, 'Vaccine Init', NULL, 'vaccine-init', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bIP0XkJR7pw', 'HPL\'s Vaccine Manufacturing Unit is a three-level facility dedicated to human vaccine production, adhering to DGDA-approved GMP standards with plans for WHO certification. Established in 2012, the facility spans 415 sq. meters and operates advanced machinery, including vial filling, lyophilizing, and crimping machines. It employs a team of 13 staff and follows international QMS guidelines, ensuring top-tier quality through systems like eQMS, DMS, and LMS. The unit focuses on producing vaccines efficiently while maintaining stringent quality control, supported by a dedicated R&D and QC department for continuous innovation in vaccine development.', '<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Healthcare Pharmaceuticals Limited (HPL) has extended its expertise in the production of generic medicines by establishing a dedicated Vaccine Manufacturing Unit. This facility is designed to meet both current and future demands in the vaccine sector, reflecting HPL&rsquo;s commitment to contributing to global healthcare.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>The Vaccine Unit consists of a three-level building equipped with modern facilities to ensure efficient and high-quality production. The ground floor (Level-1) is allocated for vaccine manufacturing, featuring a dedicated system for material loading/unloading, HVAC systems, water distribution, and utilities. Additionally, the nearby utility building supports the operational needs of this facility. The unit is compliant with GMP standards, approved by the Directorate General of Drug Administration (DGDA) under the Ministry of Health &amp; Family Welfare of Bangladesh, with plans to gain WHO certification in the future.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>HPL focuses on producing human vaccines, operating within a facility that spans a 415 square meter floor area. Since its establishment in December 2012, HPL has grown steadily in the vaccine field. By July 2013, the company had successfully initiated Metered Dose Inhaler (MDI) production, and by January 2016, the production of Dry Powder Inhalers (DPI) was underway.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>The facility&rsquo;s workforce consists of a management team of two professionals and a non-management team of eleven individuals. Together, they ensure that the production processes run smoothly and efficiently, adhering to the highest industry standards.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>HPL has equipped the unit with advanced machinery to streamline vaccine production. Notable equipment includes the Dispensing Booth from China, the Colanar Vial Filling Machine from Germany, capable of processing 1,500 vials per hour, and a PFS Filling Machine from Spain, which also operates at a capacity of 1,500 units per hour. Additionally, a Lyophilizer from China, with a capacity of 4,800 vials per cycle, ensures that the freeze-drying process for vaccines is both efficient and reliable. The unit also includes Vial and PFS Labeling Machines from Taiwan, capable of handling 5,000 vials per hour, and a Vial Crimping Machine from India, with a capacity of 3,000 vials per hour.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>To maintain its high standards of production, HPL adheres to a robust Quality Management System (QMS). The system follows international guidelines, including EudraLex Volume 4, 21 CFR 210 &amp; 211, PIC/S, ANVISA, WHO, ICH, and ISO standards. HPL rigorously monitors aspects such as deviation, change control, quality risk management, and customer complaints. The company is also working towards a paperless QMS, using advanced tools like eQMS, DMS, and LMS to improve efficiency. All finished products are released through SAP.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Furthermore, HPL has established a dedicated R&amp;D and QC facility specifically for vaccine products, underlining its commitment to research and development. This initiative allows HPL to innovate continuously and maintain high quality in vaccine manufacturing.</strong></p>', 'dafault.png', '2024-10-06 09:38:08', '2024-10-06 09:38:08'),
(15, 'MDI & DPI Unit', NULL, 'mdi-dpi-unit', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=q3PPJYpDy68', 'HPL\'s Inhaler Unit is a dedicated facility for the production of Metered Dose Inhalers (MDI) and Dry Powder Inhalers (DPI), operating under DGDA-approved GMP standards. Established in December 2012, the unit spans 470 sq. meters and employs 16 staff. Key machinery includes the Pamasol MDI Filling Machine and Capsule Filling Machine, enabling efficient production. HPL adheres to stringent Quality Management System (QMS) guidelines, incorporating tools for quality assurance and transitioning to a paperless system. The dedicated R&D department ensures ongoing innovation and compliance with local product guidelines, reinforcing HPL\'s commitment to quality healthcare solutions.', '<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Healthcare Pharmaceuticals Limited (HPL) has established a state-of-the-art Inhaler Unit for the production of Metered Dose Inhalers (MDI) and Dry Powder Inhalers (DPI). This facility underscores HPL&#39;s commitment to innovation and quality in respiratory therapies.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>The Inhaler Unit comprises a three-level building, with Level-1 (Ground Floor) dedicated to manufacturing inhaler products. This floor is equipped with an independent and dedicated material loading/unloading system, an HVAC system, a comprehensive water supply system, and a distribution system. Adequate firefighting equipment is also in place to mitigate any potential hazards.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>HPL&rsquo;s Inhaler Unit is compliant with Good Manufacturing Practices (GMP) as approved by the Directorate General of Drug Administration (DGDA), under the Ministry of Health &amp; Family Welfare of Bangladesh. Currently, there are no immediate plans for additional GMP certifications.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>The facility specializes in producing two primary product types: Metered Dose Inhalers and Dry Powder Inhalers. Spanning a 470 square meter floor area, the unit is well-designed to facilitate efficient production workflows.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Since its establishment in December 2012, HPL has focused on continuous improvement and expansion. The production of Metered Dose Inhalers began in July 2013, followed by Dry Powder Inhaler manufacturing in January 2016.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>The unit&#39;s workforce consists of three management staff and thirteen non-management employees, collectively ensuring optimal operational efficiency and adherence to quality standards.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>To support its manufacturing processes, HPL has equipped the unit with advanced machinery. Notable equipment includes the Dispensing Booth sourced from Singapore, the Pamasol MDI Filling Machine from Switzerland, which can fill 600 units per hour, and a Capsule Filling Machine from India with a capacity of 25,000 capsules per hour. Additionally, a Blister Machine from India complements the production process with a capacity of 1,500 units per hour.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>To uphold the highest quality standards, HPL adheres to a rigorous Quality Management System (QMS). The QMS follows internationally recognized guidelines, including EudraLex Volume 4, 21 CFR 210 &amp; 211, PIC/S, ANVISA, WHO, ICH, and ISO. Key tools within the QMS, such as deviation management, change control, quality risk management, and product complaint tracking, are meticulously monitored. HPL is also transitioning towards a paperless Quality Management System through the implementation of eQMS, DMS, and LMS solutions. Finished products are released through the SAP system.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Furthermore, HPL maintains a proactive Research and Development (R&amp;D) department focused on local products, ensuring that all activities align with current regulatory guidelines. This strategic emphasis on R&amp;D enables HPL to innovate and improve its inhaler products continually.</strong></p>', 'dafault.png', '2024-10-06 09:40:49', '2024-10-06 09:40:49'),
(16, 'Cream & Ointment Unit', NULL, 'cream-ointment-unit', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1Is2w8AeveA', 'HPL\'s Cream & Ointment Unit specializes in manufacturing creams, ointments, and medicated gels within a 605 m² facility approved by the DGDA for Good Manufacturing Practices. Established in 2010, the unit employs 4 management and 22 non-management staff. It features key machinery, including a 300 L Adam Manufacturing Vessel and a Yantai Chuangjia Tube Filling Machine with a capacity of 2000 tubes/hour. A new facility for topical production is under conceptual design, planned for establishment by 2026, reinforcing HPL\'s commitment to quality healthcare solutions in the local market.', '<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>The Cream &amp; Ointment Unit at HPL is dedicated to the production and packaging of topical products, including creams, ointments, and medicated gels. The existing Topical Production Facility is designed to meet health and safety standards, equipped with a HVAC and water system to ensure optimal production conditions. Future plans are in place for a new facility dedicated to topical production, which is currently under conceptual design and development, with an expected establishment date by 2026.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>The unit operates under the Good Manufacturing Practices (GMP) approved by the local regulatory authority, the Directorate General of Drug Administration (DGDA). At present, there are no plans for additional GMP certifications.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>The facility specializes in manufacturing three main types of products: creams, ointments, and gels. The production area comprises a single floor with a total dimension of 605 square meters, ensuring adequate space for efficient manufacturing processes.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Established in 2010, the Cream &amp; Ointment Unit was created to meet the demand for topical products in the local market, demonstrating HPL&#39;s commitment to providing quality healthcare solutions.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>The workforce for this unit consists of 4 management personnel and 22 non-management staff, who collectively ensure that production runs smoothly while adhering to the highest standards of quality.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>To support the manufacturing process, the facility is equipped with advanced machinery. Notable equipment includes the Adam Manufacturing and Storage Vessel from India, with a capacity of 300 liters, and the Yantai Chuangjia Tube Filling and Sealing Machine from China, capable of filling and sealing 2000 tubes per hour.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>In summary, HPL&rsquo;s Cream &amp; Ointment Unit combines modern technology, skilled manpower, and a commitment to quality, positioning itself to meet current and future demands for topical pharmaceuticals in the region.</strong></p>', 'dafault.png', '2024-10-06 09:44:06', '2024-10-06 09:44:06'),
(17, 'Cephalosporin Unit', NULL, 'cephalosporin-unit', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wGdrwA0AVuY', 'HPL\'s Cephalosporin Unit consists of three production floors: Level 1 for sterile products, Level 2 for solid products, and Level 3 (under design) for Penem group sterile products. Approved by DGDA, the facility will pursue TGA and ANVISA certifications. It manufactures tablets, capsules, powder for suspension, and powder for injection within 1672.25 m² per floor. Established in December 2019, the unit employs 171 staff. Advanced machinery includes a Macofar Vial Washing Machine and Bosch Capsule Filling Machine, ensuring high production efficiency and adherence to quality standards.', '<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>The Cephalosporin Unit at HPL is a state-of-the-art facility designed for the production of various pharmaceutical products. The facility comprises three production floors, each dedicated to specific manufacturing processes. Level 1 is primarily used for the manufacturing of sterile products, ensuring that stringent quality and safety standards are met. Level 2 focuses on the production of solid dosage forms, while Level 3, which is currently under design, will specialize in the manufacturing of the Penem group of sterile products.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>This facility is equipped with an independent and dedicated material loading and unloading system, as well as a comprehensive HVAC system to maintain optimal environmental conditions for the production processes. Additionally, a robust water system ensures that all water used in manufacturing meets the required quality standards. To safeguard the production area from potential hazards, fire-fighting equipment is strategically placed throughout the facility.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>The Cephalosporin Unit is approved by the DGDA (Directorate General of Drug Administration) under the Ministry of Health &amp; Family Welfare, Government of the People&rsquo;s Republic of Bangladesh. The facility is also working towards obtaining certifications from TGA (Therapeutic Goods Administration) in Australia and ANVISA (Ag&ecirc;ncia Nacional de Vigil&acirc;ncia Sanit&aacute;ria) in Brazil to enhance its global market reach.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>In terms of product offerings, the unit manufactures a diverse range of pharmaceutical products, including tablets, capsules, powder for suspension, and powder for injection. Each production floor has a spacious area of 1672.25 m&sup2;, allowing for efficient workflows and adherence to Good Manufacturing Practices (GMP).</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>The establishment of this facility in December 2019 marked a significant milestone in HPL&#39;s commitment to providing high-quality pharmaceutical products. Production activities for powder for injection commenced in January 2020, followed by the manufacturing of tablets, capsules, and powder for suspension starting in July 2021.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Currently, the Cephalosporin Unit employs a total of 171 staff, including management and non-management personnel, ensuring that the production processes are supervised and executed by trained professionals. The facility is equipped with advanced machinery to enhance production efficiency and quality. Notable equipment includes the Macofar Vial Washing, Depyrogenation, Filling, and Crimping Machine sourced from Italy, capable of handling 12,000 vials per hour. Other essential machines include an Autoclave Machine, an External Vial Washing Machine, and a Bosch Capsule Filling and Closing Machine with a capacity of 30,000 capsules per hour.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>With such advanced capabilities and a commitment to quality, the Cephalosporin Unit is poised to become a leader in the production of cephalosporin antibiotics, contributing to HPL&#39;s mission of delivering high-quality medicines that meet both local and international standards.</strong></p>', 'dafault.png', '2024-10-06 09:47:34', '2024-10-06 09:47:34'),
(18, 'Warehouse', NULL, 'warehouse', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=oos2kACBTh4', 'The warehouse, spanning approximately 2000 sq. m, connects to the oral solid manufacturing building via a dedicated corridor, featuring two airlocks for efficient material transfer. It comprises three fire-walled sections for receiving and storing raw materials, equipped with a central air conditioning and fire protection system, with a capacity for 800 pallets. A secondary area allows for 700 pallets. Dedicated zones exist for Cephalosporin APIs, with strict custody controls. The flammable materials section is designed to prevent fire hazards. Additionally, it includes a sampling area, offices, a battery charging area, and storage for rejected and returned goods.', '<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>The warehouse, covering approximately 2000 sq. m, is strategically connected to the general oral solid manufacturing building via a dedicated corridor, ensuring efficient material transfer through two airlocks: one for raw and primary packaging materials and another for secondary packaging materials. The facility is divided into three fire-walled sections: one for receiving materials, another for storing raw and primary packaging materials equipped with a central air conditioning and fire protection system with a five-level racking system and a total pallet capacity of 800. Designated quarantine and approved materials areas are maintained according to required storage conditions.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>A secondary packaging area features a similar five-level racking system with a capacity of 700 pallets, alongside controlled areas for rejected and returned materials. A raw material sampling area follows cGMP principles, ensuring separate entry for materials and personnel, complete with proper change rooms.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>The Cephalosporin APIs are managed within designated areas of the warehouse, where they are received, stored, and dispatched for manufacturing, while finished products are stored under strict custody. No handling or exposure of cephalosporin API or finished products occurs outside these dedicated zones.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>The flammable material warehouse, located at the southeast corner of the main facility, is segmented into three rooms designed to prevent fire and explosions, equipped to confine water for emergency situations.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Overall, the warehouse for general products includes:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li dir=\"ltr\">\r\n	<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>A large loading/unloading bay.</strong></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li dir=\"ltr\">\r\n	<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>A receiving area.</strong></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li dir=\"ltr\">\r\n	<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Dedicated storage areas for raw, packaging, and finished goods based on specific storage conditions, including:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li dir=\"ltr\">\r\n		<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Ambient condition storage.</strong></p>\r\n		</li>\r\n		<li dir=\"ltr\">\r\n		<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Temperature-controlled storage (below 30&deg;C).</strong></p>\r\n		</li>\r\n		<li dir=\"ltr\">\r\n		<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Temperature and humidity-controlled storage (15&deg;C to 25&deg;C and RH 45% to 65%).</strong></p>\r\n		</li>\r\n		<li dir=\"ltr\">\r\n		<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Cold storage (8-15&deg;C and 2-8&deg;C).</strong></p>\r\n		</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li dir=\"ltr\">\r\n	<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>A sampling area equipped with a laminar airflow (LAF) system.</strong></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li dir=\"ltr\">\r\n	<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>An office for logistics and lockers for personnel.</strong></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li dir=\"ltr\">\r\n	<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>A battery charging area for forklifts.</strong></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li dir=\"ltr\">\r\n	<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>A dedicated area for narcotic materials.</strong></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li dir=\"ltr\">\r\n	<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Rejected material and return goods storage areas.</strong></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>', 'dafault.png', '2024-10-06 10:36:32', '2024-10-06 10:36:32'),
(19, 'HVAC', NULL, 'hvac', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=oos2kACBTh4', 'HPL’s HVAC system is vital for maintaining GMP-compliant environments across its production units and QC area. The General Solid Unit features nine air handling units with comprehensive heating, cooling, and humidity control systems. The Cephalosporin Unit operates with three dedicated units for precise temperature and humidity management. The Semi-solid Unit uses two air handling units, while the Sterile Unit is equipped with ten units, including pre-cooling and de-humidification systems. These tailored HVAC setups ensure optimal air quality and safety, supporting HPL’s commitment to producing high-quality pharmaceutical products.', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The <strong>HVAC System</strong> at HPL plays a crucial role in maintaining the environmental conditions necessary for the production of pharmaceutical products in compliance with Good Manufacturing Practices (GMP). Each production unit and the Quality Control (QC) area have dedicated and separated HVAC systems to ensure optimal air quality, temperature, and humidity levels, which are essential for both product integrity and personnel safety.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align:justify\">General Solid Unit</h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">In the General Solid Unit, the HVAC system is equipped with <strong>nine separate air handling units</strong> designed according to the Zone Plan. The system features a comprehensive setup that includes:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Four heating systems</strong> to maintain appropriate temperature levels.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Seven individual return fans</strong> to ensure proper air circulation within the unit.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Six individual exhaust fans</strong> for effective removal of contaminants and maintaining air quality.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Four individual de-humidifiers</strong> to control humidity levels, preventing moisture-related issues during production.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Two individual wet de-duster systems</strong> to remove particulate matter from the air.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Three individual chillers</strong> for cooling purposes, and</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Four individual chilled water circulation pumps</strong> to ensure efficient distribution of chilled water throughout the system.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align:justify\">Cephalosporin Unit</h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The Cephalosporin Unit&#39;s HVAC system consists of <strong>three separate air handling units</strong>, specifically designed to cater to the unit&#39;s unique requirements. This includes:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Two heating systems</strong> to provide the necessary warmth.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Two individual return fans</strong> for air circulation.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>One individual exhaust fan</strong> to maintain air quality.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>One individual de-humidifier</strong> to control humidity.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>One individual wet de-duster system</strong> for particulate removal.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Three individual chillers</strong> for cooling, alongside</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Four individual chilled water circulation pumps</strong> to facilitate efficient chilled water distribution.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align:justify\">Semi-solid Unit</h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The HVAC system for the Semi-solid Unit operates with <strong>two separate air handling units</strong>, specifically designed to maintain optimal environmental conditions for the production of semi-solid dosage forms. The configuration supports effective air circulation and temperature control, although specific details of components are simplified due to the lesser complexity compared to other units.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align:justify\">Sterile Unit</h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The Sterile Unit has a robust HVAC system that includes <strong>ten separate air handling units</strong> as dictated by the Zone Plan. This setup comprises:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Four pre-cooling systems</strong> to initially reduce air temperature before it enters the main air handling units.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Four individual de-humidifiers</strong> to maintain the required low humidity levels necessary for sterile production environments.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">By implementing these specialized HVAC systems across different units, HPL ensures a controlled environment that meets strict GMP standards. This not only supports the production of high-quality pharmaceutical products but also enhances the overall safety and efficacy of operations within the facility. The commitment to maintaining optimal air quality and environmental conditions is integral to HPL&#39;s mission of providing safe and effective medications to its customers.</p>', 'dafault.png', '2024-10-06 10:40:17', '2024-10-06 10:40:17');
