(4, 'To be the leading pharmaceutical company in Bangladesh in terms of expertise, innovation, and responsible entrepreneurship. We aim to establish a visible presence in international markets with our high-quality products and services.', 'To preserve and improve patients\' health by consistently delivering high-quality, safe, and effective pharmaceutical products and services that meet customer expectations across the globe through current good manufacturing practices, state-of-the-art technology, a competent workforce, and efficient management.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2024-09-23 11:14:02', 'Vission and Mission', '', 'default.png'),
(5, 'Healthcare Pharmaceuticals Ltd. (HPL) is one of the leading pharmaceutical companies in Bangladesh, certified by international pharmaceutical regulatory authorities such as TGA (Australia), NPRA (Malaysia), MCAZ (Zimbabwe), TFDA (Tanzania), and others.', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">HPL focuses on innovation and delivers healthcare solutions that improve and extend people&rsquo;s lives. From prevention to treatment, HPL transforms scientific innovation into healthcare solutions in areas such as Antihistamines, Antiemetics, Anti-diabetics, Analgesics and Antipyretics, Anti-infectives, Bone Care, Biotech and Oncology, CNS Drugs, Cardiovascular, Dermatological Products, Respiratory Care, Ophthalmics, Vitamins &amp; Minerals, and many more. Healthcare Pharmaceuticals Ltd. began its journey in 1988 by establishing Healthcare Distribution Limited in association with Roche Limited, a renowned Switzerland-based multinational company. Until 2001, HPL was responsible for importing and distributing Roche products to the local market. In 1996, HPL decided to establish its own pharmaceutical plant to produce products that were being imported from Roche, Switzerland, as well as other local generics for the domestic market. Today, Healthcare Pharmaceuticals is the fastest-growing organization in Bangladesh&#39;s pharmaceutical industry. We are currently producing over Four hundred products in various dosage forms, including Tablets, Capsules, Liquids, Dry Syrups, Creams &amp; Ointments, Gels, Small Volume Parenterals, and Eye Drops, covering almost all therapeutic classes. Numerous products are also in the pipeline for launch in both local and international markets across Asia, Africa, and the CIS region.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2024-10-15 14:27:57', 'About Us', '', 'default.png'),
(6, NULL, '<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>HPL is committed to transforming local efforts into global achievements. Our first step toward international collaboration was a licensing agreement with F. Hoffmann-La Roche Limited, Basel, Switzerland.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">In 2005, we further expanded our international presence by signing an agreement with Novartis (Sandoz) Bangladesh Limited, allowing us to produce their products at our facility under a toll manufacturing agreement. That same year, we successfully passed a global quality audit by Roche, Switzerland, marking the beginning of our exports to several Asian countries, including Myanmar, Vietnam, Sri Lanka, Hong Kong, and Bhutan. We have also established strategic partnerships with various countries across Africa, ASEAN, and the CIS regions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>HPL is currently in the process of securing GMP approvals from esteemed regulatory bodies such as UKMHRA, TGA, and GCC. We continue to leverage our expertise to explore global opportunities and strengthen international collaborations.</strong></p>', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZVZWzQeCUjM', NULL, NULL, '2024-10-14 09:04:57', 'Global Operations', '', '-2024-10-06-67026ec52ed96.gif'),
